result.execSummary:
The defendant Kodiak D Young was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: No contact with Jama D., Alyssa W., or James T., or their families or residences. No controlled substances or alcohol; urine screens.
Be given literacy training. Obtain GED. Seek and maintain employment. Be given job and vocational training. Cognitive thinking intervention counseling.
Pay stipulated restitution to Alyssa W. in the amount of $2,200.00 and $57.02 to James T.

Pay DNA surcharge, fine, costs, fees, and assessments.  Should defendant get revoked and be sent to prison, the Court ordered monies taken from prison funds not to exceed 25% to be collected by the DOC.  Balance would be paid while on extended supervision.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Defendant Kodiak D Young in court with attorney Richard J Carpenter.  Kimberly D Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel advised the State that they will proceed to plea only on today's date and be requesting a presentence report.  Victim present in court and made aware of same.  Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  On defense request, Court ordered a presentence investigation.  Order for Presentence Investigation signed and filed.  Court ordered Justice Point and all terms and conditions of bail are to continue.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 10, 2014 at 08:30 am.
